    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-18T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-18T19:00:00-05:00" n="264"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/12390: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-19T00:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 19, 1918—12 midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received November 20—11:58
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5920. Department’s number 6282, November 15th. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PS1"
                        >Pichon</persName> informs me in principle the French Government is willing
                    to have China represented on the Supreme War Council, whenever questions
                    involving China are concerned, but that he felt permission should be formally
                    granted only upon the joint recommendation of France, Italy, Great Britain and
                    the United States. He expressed the belief there would be no objection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
